-- GM Europe spokesman says three offers in for Opel
-- 
-- Wed May 20, 2009 4:28pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/05/20/us-gm-opel-three-idUSBAT00292320090520

 

 FRANKFURT  (Reuters) - A spokesman for the European wing of struggling carmaker General Motors ( GM.N ) confirmed on Wednesday it had received three offers for its German unit Opel. 

 "Three offers have arrived," the GM Europe spokesman said when asked about the widely expected bids from Italy's Fiat ( FIA.MI ), Canadian-Austrian car parts group Magna MGa.TO and investment firm RHJ International. (Reporting by Angelika Gruber, writing by Brian Rohan)